---
// File: src/pages/terms.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="ZiiU — Terms">
  <div class="kicker">Terms</div>
  <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
  <p>
    These Terms explain how ZiiU works and what we expect from users. Our goal is simple:
    create a safe, respectful environment where young people can learn and grow.
  </p>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:18px;">
    <h3>1) Who can use ZiiU</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      ZiiU is designed for ages 9–17. Depending on your location, a parent or guardian may need to provide consent
      for account creation or certain features. Schools or programs may also provide access under applicable rules.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <h3>2) What ZiiU is (and is not)</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      <strong>ZiiU is:</strong> a structured self-growth and life navigation tool.<br />
      <strong>ZiiU is not:</strong> therapy, emergency services, or a substitute for professional care.
      If someone is in immediate danger, call local emergency services right away.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <h3>3) Respectful use</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      Users must not: harass others, share harmful content, attempt to bypass safety systems, or use ZiiU for illegal purposes.
      We may restrict or terminate access to protect users and the platform.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <h3>4) Safety and moderation</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      ZiiU may use moderation and safety tools to reduce harmful or inappropriate content. We may take action when content
      or behavior threatens safety, violates these Terms, or disrupts the platform.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <h3>5) Account responsibility</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      Keep login information private. If you think your account has been compromised, contact us. Parents/guardians and school
      administrators should ensure accounts are used appropriately within their environment.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <h3>6) Content you provide</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      You own the content you create. By using ZiiU, you give us permission to process the content you submit
      to provide the service (for example, to generate insights and suggestions).
      We do not claim ownership of your personal reflections.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <h3>7) Service changes</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      ZiiU will evolve over time. We may change features to improve safety, performance, or user experience.
      If changes materially affect these Terms, we will update this page.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <h3>8) Disclaimers</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      ZiiU provides guidance for personal growth and education. We do not guarantee outcomes.
      Always use good judgment and involve a trusted adult when needed.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <h3>9) Contact</h3>
    <p style="margin:0;">
      Questions about these Terms? Email: <strong>support@ziiu.ai</strong> (replace with your preferred email).
    </p>
  </div>

  <p style="margin-top:18px; font-size:14px; color:#486175;">
    By using ZiiU, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the service.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-top:16px; display:flex; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <a class="btn primary" href="/get">Join Early Access</a>
    <a class="btn ghost" href="/privacy">Read Privacy</a>
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
